    <briefdescription>
<para>A class which provides an implementation of a Crank-Nicolson method. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>A class which provides an implementation of a Crank-Nicolson method in order to evolve values over time. This specialisation handles elementwise operations and can be called from GPU.</para>
<para>For the following ODE : <formula id="398">$\partial_t y(t) = f(t, y(t)) $</formula>,</para>
<para>the Crank-Nicolson method is given by : <formula id="399">$ y^{k} =  y^{n} + \frac{dt}{2} \left(f(t^{n}, y^{n}) + f(t^{k}, y^{k}) \right)$</formula>.</para>
<para>The method is an implicit method. If <formula id="400">$ |y^{k+1} -  y^{k}| &lt; \varepsilon $</formula>, then we set <formula id="401">$ y^{n+1} = y^{k+1} $</formula>.</para>
<para>The method is order 2. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
